The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party has approved the timetable and schedule of activities for the conduct of ward, local government areas and state congresses in Yobe State for the purpose of electing new ward, LGA and state executive committee members in the state. This was contained in a statement by the National Organising Secretary of the PDP, Col Austin Akobundu (retd.). According to the approved timetable, ward congresses to elect ward executive and three ad hoc delegates have been slated for Wednesday, April 7, 2021, while screening of state exco aspirants and ward congresses appeals have been scheduled for April 8 and April 9, respectively. In the same vein, the local government congresses to elect LGA executive and national delegates have been fixed for April 10, while LGA Congress appeals and screening of State executives are slated for April 11, 2021. The State Congress to elect state executive officers has been scheduled for Monday, April 12, while State Congress Appeals has been slated for Wednesday, April 14, 2021.